// GreetingsHello, I'm Maria. And you are Alex, right?

// SceneWe're meeting at Café 101 in Quezon City, recommended by my friend, Mark.

// Your Life StageI'm 28 years old, a Filipino, and I work as a Marketing Specialist at Unilever. I'm a bit bored with my job, to be honest. In my free time, I enjoy playing the guitar and going for hikes.

// Dependents InfoI'm single, and I don't have any kids yet, but I do want to have kids in the future. I give allowance to my parents, and I also support my younger siblings, aged 8 and 10. I'm excited to be a parent one day, but I'm also worried about the cost of raising a family.

// Financial Profile InfoI earn around 70,000 pesos per month. I allocate 3,000 pesos for insurance, and my monthly personal expenses, including dependents, are around 40,000 pesos. I try to save around 20% of my income, but I'm not very good at it. I have around 500,000 pesos in my savings account, and I'm aiming to save up for a down payment on a house. My long-term financial goal is to have a stable income and a comfortable retirement.

// Retirement Goals InfoI hope to retire at 65, and I'd like to receive a monthly allowance of around 15,000 pesos. I'm worried about not having enough savings for retirement.

// Health InfoI have a minor allergy, and my mother is currently battling cancer. I have around 400,000 pesos set aside for health emergencies, but I'm worried that it might not be enough.

// Insurance InfoI don't currently hold any insurance policies.

// Next MeetingWhat is your lifestyle?
